devdoc.details: NFTs can be packed with fungible tokens, and can have special features I.E. collaborators and separate creatorship and ownership

addAllowedMinter(address).details: Add a minter to the approved list to mint tokens

params.hash: Hash of the token to add the collaborator to

addSingleCollaborator(uint256,address).details: Add a collaborator to a single token (like land)

balanceOfHash(address,string).details: Get the number of tokens associated with a specific hash held by the token owner For example, if collaborators are working on a token series, this would return all of them for one collaborator

params.owner: Address of the owner of the token

returns._0: Return the balance as a number of tokens Example args: 0x08E242bB06D85073e69222aF8273af419d19E4f6, 0x1

baseURI().details: Returns the base URI set via {_setBaseURI}. This will be automatically added as a prefix in {tokenURI} to each token's URI, or to the token ID if no specific URI is set for that token ID.

params._erc20Contract: ERC20 contract attached to fungible tokens
params._isPublicallyMintable: Whether anyone can mint tokens with this contract I.E. collaborators and separate creatorship and ownership
params._isSingleIssue: Whether the token is single issue (name based) or no (hash based)
params.name: Name of the contract (default is "NFT")

params.hash: Hash of the token to get collaborators for

getHash(uint256).details: Get the hash of a token by ID

params.tokenId: Token to get the hash from

returns._0: Returns a string containing the token hash

getMetadata(string,string).details: Get metadata for the token. Metadata is a key-value store that can be set by owners and collaborators

params.hash: Token hash to query for metadata
params.key: Key to query for a value

getMinter(uint256).details: Get the address for for the minter of the token

params.tokenId: ID of the token we are querying

getPackedBalance(uint256).details: Get the balance of fungible tokens packed into this non-fungible token

params.tokenId: ID of the non-fungible ERC721 token
Token ID of the token to get collaborators for

getSingleMetadata(uint256,string).details: Get metadata for a single token (non-hashed)

params.tokenId: Token hash to add metadata to

returns._0: Returns the value stored for the key

getTokenIdsOf(address).details: List the tokens IDs owned by an account

isAllowedMinter(address).details: Check if an account is allowed to mint tokens

returns._0: Returns true if the acount can mint

isCollaborator(string,address).details: Check is an address has access as a collaborator (for development of a token between multiple users)

params.hash: Hash of the token to test

returns._0: Returns true if the address is a collaborator on this token

isSingleCollaborator(uint256,address).details: Check if this address is a collaborator on a single issue token (like land)

returns._0: Returns true if the address is a collaborator on the token

mint(address,string,string,string,string.details: Mint one or more non-fungible tokens with this contract The count parameter is what is looped over to create the token. This means the higher the count, the higher the gas. This is the main reason that we can only mint so many tokens at once.

params.description: Description of the token (set by user)
params.ext: File extension of the token Example: "png"
params.hash: Hash of the file to mint Example: 0x1
params.name: Name of the token
params.to: Address of who is receiving the token on mint Example: 0x08E242bB06D85073e69222aF8273af419d19E4f6

mintSingle(address,string).details: Mint one non-fungible tokens with this contract

params.hash: Hash of the file to mint
params.to: Address of who is receiving the token on mint Example: 0x08E242bB06D85073e69222aF8273af419d19E4f6

mintTokenId(address,uint256).details: Mint a token with a specific ID

params.to: Who should receive the minted token
params.tokenId: ID of the token to mint (ie: 250)

pack(address,uint256,uint256).details: Pack fungible tokens into this non-fungible token

params.from: Address of who is packing the token

removeAllowedMinter(address).details: Remove a minter from the approved list to mint tokens

params.hash: Hash of the token to remove the collaborator from

removeSingleCollaborator(uint256,address.details: Remove a collaborator from a single token (like land)

seal(string).details: Seal the token forever and remove collaborators so that it can't be altered

setBaseURI(string).details: Set the base URI for this contract

setMetadata(string,string,string).details: Set metadata for the token. Metadata is a key-value store that can be set by owners and collaborators

params.hash: Token hash to add metadata to

setSingleMetadata(uint256,string,string).details: Set metadata for a single token (non-hashed)

params.tokenId: Token hash to add metadata to

startTokenIdOfHash(string).details: Get the start token id of a hash

returns._0: Start of token id for this hash

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}. Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

tokenByIdFull(uint256).details: Get the complete information for a token from it's ID

returns._0: Returns true if the token exists

tokenOfOwnerByIndexFull(address,uint256).details: Get the full Token struct from an owner address at a specific index

params.index: Index in owner's balance to query

tokenURI(uint256).details: Get the URI of a token

params.tokenId: Token to get the URI from (ie: 250)

returns._0: URI of the token to retrieve

totalSupplyOfHash(string).details: Get the total supply of a hash

unpack(address,uint256,uint256).details: Unpack fungible tokens from this non-fungible token

params.to: Address of who is packing the token

updateHash(string,string).details: Update token hash with a new hash

devdoc.title: Extension of {ERC721} for Webaverse non-fungible tokens
